    <stitle>International&#174; MaxxForce&#8482; 7 Engine Service Manual - Power Cylinders - Installation</stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec id="s14.4">
        <title>Installation</title>
        <svcproc id="s14.4.1" svcproctype="install" graphiccount="4">
            <title>Piston Assembly</title>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To prevent personal injury or death, wear safety glasses with side shields when doing the
                        following procedure.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="f3450014017" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figd04/D0423.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="192px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Correct position of installed connecting rod</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Longer leg of connecting rod (cam side)</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">CAM SIDE stamp on cam side of piston crown</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Connect piston to connecting rod as follows:</para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Lubricate connecting rod piston pin bore, piston pin bore, and piston pin with clean
                        engine oil.
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Position the longer leg of the connecting rod with the side of the piston showing
                        the CAM SIDE stamped in its crown.
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Place connecting rod into piston.</para>
                    <figure id="f3450014018" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic filename="../figM04/M04107.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                                 scalefitheight="192px" box="no"/>
                        <caption>Piston pin retainer ring</caption>
                    </figure>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Using a suitable tool, install piston pin retainer ring at one end of piston pin
                        bore.
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Slide piston pin through bored holes, stopping at installed piston pin retainer
                        ring.
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Use a suitable tool to install second piston pin retainer ring.</para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Check the
                        <hotlnk document="eges3451_297.xml" xrefid="s14.t1">piston pin end clearance</hotlnk>
                        <xref refid="s14.t1"/>.
                    </para>
                </step2>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f3450014019" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figd04/D0401.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="192px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Piston rings installed</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Piston ring expansion pliers</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Piston</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Piston ring (top compression ring shown)</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>To prevent engine damage, install piston rings correctly. Both intermediate and compression
                        rings have the same identification markings. The marking must face up for the ring to be
                        installed correctly. The intermediate ring has a rectangular cross section and goes in the
                        middle groove. The top compression ring has a keystone cross section and goes in the top groove.
                    </para>
                </caution>
                <note>
                    <para>Only expand piston rings enough to fit over top of piston.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Use
                    <hotlnk document="eges3451_299.xml" xrefid="s14.t3">piston ring expansion pliers</hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="s14.t3"/>
                    to install piston rings.
                </para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Install expansion spring component of two piece oil control ring into bottom piston
                        groove.
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Install oil scraper component of two piece oil control ring over expansion spring
                        with the gap 180&#176; from the spring wire latch.
                    </para>
                    <figure id="f3450014020" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic filename="../figd04/D0414.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                                 scalefitheight="192px" box="no"/>
                        <caption>Piston ring identification mark (top compression ring)</caption>
                        <calloutgroup>
                            <callout1 type="arabic">Identification mark</callout1>
                        </calloutgroup>
                    </figure>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Install intermediate ring into middle piston groove. Make sure ring is installed
                        with identification mark facing up.
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Install top compression ring into top piston groove. Make sure ring is installed
                        with identification mark facing up.
                    </para>
                </step2>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Space ring gaps approximately 120&#176; apart after ring installation.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
